page.title: 01Wensum Valley&Felthorpe Wood
page.content: The river Wensum flows in the valley. Surrounding grassland is used for grazing cattle. Higher ground is used for agriculture growing mainly barley & sugar beet. Some wheat, dwarf beans, potatoes & carrots are also grown, as are daffodils for the bulbs. Away from the arable, woodland takes over being naturally deciduous, but some has been managed & planted with conifers. Employment in the area is in agricul- ture & for a builders merchant & a garden centre. Some small self employed industries also exist, concrete products, printing, pet farm. Many people living in the area work outside of it. A small private flying club operates there. The old school & railway station are now dwellings & a few new dwellings have been built but no estate type development exists keeping the village character of area.
